#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "The goal of gcompris-teachers is to enable teachers to:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "create and manage pupils groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "create specific work plans."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "connect and send a work plan to pupils."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "visualize the work results per group and pupil."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "analyse pupils answers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following section describes the different screens implementing these "
"functionalities."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main screen overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid "The main screen allows to access:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dashboard page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manage pupils page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Connect devices page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Follow activities results page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manage datasets page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Display results as charts page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid "Settings page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default the Dashboard page is shown, containing the login dialog, and the "
"side menu bar to access the other pages is hidden until a teacher account is "
"logged in."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The GCompris Teachers main screen showing the dashboard and login interface."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A button to show/hide the title of the buttons in the side menu bar (the "
"hamburger icon) allows to save some space once the user knows the meaning of "
"each icon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A view of the sidebar menu with the hamburger icon used to expand or "
"collapse the labels."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dashboard - Login dialog"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a new teacher login and database, input the name and the password. "
"You’ll then be able to choose if you want to encrypt the database (to avoid "
"anyone to read it without the password)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dialog for creating a new teacher account with a username and password "
"and choosing database encryption settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manage groups and pupils"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This page allows to create the different pupils and groups for your class."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The management screen where a teacher can view the list of groups and pupils."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a group"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on the <quote>Add a group</quote> button on the bottom left and in the "
"dialog fill the <quote>Name</quote> and optionally the <quote>Description</"
"quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dialog box to add a new pupil group by entering its name and description."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modify a group name or Delete it"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To edit or delete a group, hover it on the group list and the <quote>Edit</"
"quote> and <quote>Delete</quote> buttons will appear."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The interface showing how edit and delete buttons appear when hovering over "
"a group name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking on the <quote>Delete</quote> button will allow you to delete the "
"group. Note that the pupils will be removed from the groups but not deleted "
"from the database. If you want to remove pupils, follow the next section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The confirmation prompt asking the teacher if they are sure they want to "
"delete a group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a single pupil"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on <quote>Add a pupil</quote> to create a new pupil in the database. "
"There, you can set the pupil's name and the password to connect from the "
"clients. You can also directly add them in pre-existing groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The 'Add a pupil' window showing fields for pupil name, password, and group "
"selection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create several pupils using csv strings / Export pupils to a file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can directly import a list of pupils using a csv file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The import interface used to upload multiple pupil profiles from a CSV file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting a list of pupils is also possible:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:243
#, no-c-format
msgid "pupil_export_csv"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing pupils"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The interface also proposes buttons to edit pupils, add or remove them from "
"groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The interface showing the buttons used to assign a specific pupil to a "
"classroom group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The interface showing how to remove a pupil from their currently assigned "
"group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also delete pupils. Note that deleting a pupil does not delete its "
"group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pupil management screen highlighting the delete button for pupil "
"accounts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "Connect devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once the database is ready, it’s now time to communicate with the different "
"clients. The <quote>Connect devices</quote> page shows the different groups "
"and pupils. By default, no group is selected so all the pupils are visible. "
"Selecting a group will filter the visible pupils to only work with this "
"specific group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The 'Connect devices' dashboard displaying the status of all available "
"pupils and groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration of the server and client devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:300
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The teacher needs to configure the server and client devices they want to "
"connect to before being able to connect. All the devices need to be "
"connected on the same local network. On the server, go to the "
"<quote>Settings</quote> page and choose a unique <quote>Server ID</quote> "
"(at least unique for the local network) and a <quote>Port</quote> (if you "
"don’t know, keep the default one)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The settings page where the Server ID and Port number are configured for "
"network communication."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:315
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On GCompris devices side, go to the <quote>Configuration</quote> page from "
"the main menu, and scroll to the bottom to find the <quote>Teacher’s server "
"config</quote> button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A confirmation dialog on the pupil's device asking to connect to the "
"teacher's server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "After clicking it, make sure to have the same settings as the server:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The client-side settings screen where pupils enter the matching Server ID "
"and Port."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also, if the device running the server or the client has a firewall, make "
"sure to open the chosen port in the firewall configuration to let the "
"devices communicate."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid "Daily connection workflow"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The connection workflow is the following: <emphasis>The teacher asks the "
"pupils to switch on their devices and start GCompris, and then from the "
"<quote>Connect devices</quote> page press the <quote>Connect devices</quote> "
"button.</emphasis> On the client devices, a dialog will appear asking "
"confirmation to connect to the server. Note that client devices need to be "
"on the GCompris main menu, not on any activity or configuration page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pop-up on the pupil's device asking for permission to connect to the "
"teacher's server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After confirmation from the pupils, the teacher selects which logins they "
"want to send from the <quote>Pupils</quote> list and press <quote>Send login "
"list</quote>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The client devices will display a new dialog allowing to select the login "
"they want."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The login selection screen on the pupil device showing the list of names "
"sent by the teacher."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Once confirmed, a second dialog will open to enter the password."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The password entry dialog on the pupil device for logging into their "
"specific profile."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the password is correct, the client will see a green button on the bar "
"indicating a successful connection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The GCompris navigation bar showing a green indicator for a successful "
"server connection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid "And the server will receive a notification:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The teacher's dashboard showing color-coded status indicators for successful "
"and failed login attempts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:409
#, no-c-format
msgid "The different colors are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:412
#, no-c-format
msgid "Green: connected"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:413
#, no-c-format
msgid "Red: wrong password"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Grey: disconnected (it was connected at some point but got disconnected)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:416
#, no-c-format
msgid "Transparent: nobody tried to connect using this login."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The connection list displaying different colors for disconnected pupils "
"versus those who haven't yet connected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Activities"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This page allows to display the different results filtered by date, groups, "
"pupils and activities."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The activities results page showing filters for date, group, and specific "
"educational tasks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:442
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following image shows the results for the <quote>Vertical subtraction</"
"quote> activity (each activity which handles sending data to the server has "
"its own visualisation)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A detailed breakdown of pupil performance in the 'vertical subtraction' "
"activity, showing errors and successes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We can see the pupil entered an incorrect answer on the first try and a "
"correct answer on the second try, and the answers details to spot the errors."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid "Datasets"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:463
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The datasets page allows teachers to create/update/delete specific datasets "
"for the activities to target specific needs, and send/remove them to/from "
"the clients."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dataset management page where teachers create custom content for various "
"activities."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One limitation for now is that only activities following the GCompris "
"dataset format can be edited (so no <quote>Grammatical classes</quote> or "
"<quote>Falling words</quote> for example). You can find the list of "
"supported activities (which can send data or have a dataset editor) on this "
"page of our development wiki: <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/education/"
"gcompris/-/wikis/Teacher-administration-tool#supported-activities\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here is an example for the <quote>Binary bulbs</quote> activity. The common "
"part of all activity editors contains fields to enter the dataset name, the "
"goal and the difficulty. Then, each activity will have a specific editor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:492
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The activity editor for 'Binary bulbs' activity, allowing customization of "
"dataset names and difficulty levels."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <quote>Instructions</quote> button on the bottom left is provided to "
"give some specific information about how to fill the dataset when needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The instructions panel providing guidance on how to correctly fill out "
"custom activity data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:508
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to delete a dataset: select it, press the <quote>Remove dataset</"
"quote> button and confirm in the following dialog:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:516
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The confirmation prompt used to safely delete a custom dataset from the "
"teacher tool."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:520
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have clients connected, you may want to send them a specific dataset "
"to be available on their side. Select the dataset and press the <quote>Send "
"to clients</quote> button. The list of all the connected clients will be "
"displayed and you will be able to select which will receive it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:530
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The interface for selecting which connected pupil devices should receive a "
"new dataset."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:535
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specific activities for the server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We have created the <quote>Multiple-choice questions</quote> activity that "
"is only visible when the device contains datasets for it. This activity "
"allows teachers to create multiple-choice questionnaires on any topic."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The preview of the 'Multiple choice questions' activity on the pupil device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid "Charts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Charts page is similar to the Activities page and allows to display the "
"different results filtered by date, groups, pupils and activities as charts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The charts overview page providing a graphical visualization of pupil and "
"group progress."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For now, the visualization is really limited but will be improved depending "
"on teachers feedback. After clicking on an activity on the chart, there is a "
"view similar to what is shown on the Activities page. If the <quote>Pupils</"
"quote> tab is selected, you can see all the results for a specific pupil:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A graphical view showing the success rate and history for a specific pupil."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <quote>Activities</quote> tab is selected, you can see all the "
"results for a specific activity:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:588
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A chart displaying the overall class performance for a single selected "
"activity."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:595
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The settings page allows to customize the interface and get some information "
"on the current database and session."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The general settings page showing information about the current session."
msgstr ""

